This Oyster Perpetual Cosmograph Daytona in 18 ct yellow gold with a champagne-colour and black dial and an Oysterflex bracelet, features a Black Cerachrom bezel with tachymetric scale.





The monobloc Cerachrom bezel in high-tech ceramic offers a number of advantages: it is corrosion resistant, virtually scratchproof and the colour is unaffected by UV rays. This extremely durable bezel also offers an exceptionally legible tachymetric scale, thanks to the deposition of a thin layer of platinum in the numerals and graduation via a PVD (Physical Vapour Deposition) process. The monobloc Cerachrom bezel is made in a single piece and holds the crystal firmly in place on the middle case, ensuring waterproofness.

Bracelet material: Oysterflex


Power: 72 Hours

ABOUT


This pre-owned 2014 Omega De Ville Chronoscope 422.10.41.50.04.001 is in like new condition. The watch comes as a full set, along with additional 1 year warranty from The Watch Village.




All of our watches undergo a thorough inspection of accuracy, functionality and condition to meet our strict standards. Additionally, we check each watch against records to ensure authenticity and ownership status.




This incredibly rare De Ville features an impressive chronoscope dial that is packed with an impressive array of watchmaking complications. With the white dial being decorated with gold coloured hands and numeral markers. Surrounding which is a plain bezel, sat upon a 41mm stainless steel case and presented on a matching steel bracelet. All powered by the Omega Co-Axial Calibre 3313 automatic movement.
